snippet.textDisplay: That was one of the worst fights I have ever seen. I agree with Romero about what was given to the fans, especially paying fans. I understand doing what it takes to win but If you could have sat in the spectator seat so that you never get hit should not make you the winner of a fight. If I were judging that fight, I would have at the least scored it a draw. The ref did the right thing in trying to push the fighters to engage more but I think he should have taken a point away from Adesanya throughout the fight for running, literally running.  Believe it or not, I actually agree with Dana as well. Romero is at the end of his career. He should have run down Adesanya and pulled out all the stops to get him. No excuses for him from me either. Dana should penalize both fighters for a lack of performance on such a huge stage.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm just gonna quote Adesanya here: "It takes two to tango."
--
My thought exactly and that goes both ways, Adesanya - which is why you can't blame everything on Romero. Did he start out defensively? Yes. Were you scared of his counter and weren't attacking as much? Yes, as you yourself admitted. The thing is, you call it being smart, but he could also say he was being smart for not playing into your game plan. Who was attacking more? I honestly don't know. Both of you guys had your moments of activity and passivity. Romero was standing still, but when he exploded (especially in the first 2 rounds) he looked very dangerous. On the other hand Adesanya was slightly more active after round 3 and 4 with those leg kicks, but whenever Romero exploded Adesanya was running for his life (and I'm not blaming him for that).


With that being said, I wouldn't say the fight was boring. People who say that are just stupid. Sure, I wish the fight was a bit more active, but this was a game of nerves and tactics where both fighters wanted the other one to play into their trap. In the end, I feel Romero just didn't show enough to take the belt, but I also don't think Adesanya beat Romero. I would score the first and second round for Romero, third and fourth for Adesanya, while the fifth I just can't decide. If I was absolutely forced to chose with a gun pressed to my head, I think I would give it to Adesanya, since he is the champion and he did damage Romero's leg quite a bit, so if the fight was prolonged, I think that would play a big role.
